observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor create a committee to conduct physical inventory count of the Property, Plant and Equipment to determine actual existence of and condition of the properties pursuant to Section 124 of the NGAS Manual Volume 1; 

An updated and descriptive Property Card be maintained by the Property Office; 

Likewise, the Accounting Office is advised to maintain Property Equipment Ledger Cards as required under the NGAS to provide informative data on Property, Plant and Equipment; 

For the year 2018, the Property Officer/Municipal Treasurer is advised to start issuing Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment (ARE) for the particular property issued to employees to easily pinpoint accountability and facilitate inventory taking; and 

The cost of the school building shall be transferred to the Department of Education through a Journal Entry Voucher to be drawn by the Municipal Accountant and given to the Accountant of the DepEd.

We have recommended the following:
The Municipal Mayor create a committee to conduct physical count of inventories and PPE to determine actual existence and condition of the assets pursuant to Section 124 of the NGAS Manual Volume 1;
The property office/officer maintain property cards and ensure that the same is regularly updated;
The Accounting Office maintain Supplies and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards as required under the NGAS; and
After the conduct of physical count of PPE, the Accounting Office should compute for the depreciation using the estimated useful life under COA Circular No. 2003-007.

2.6 In view of the above observations, we have recommended the following:
The Municipal Mayor creates a committee to conduct physical inventory count of the Property, Plant and Equipment to determine actual existence and condition of the properties pursuant to Section 124 of the NGAS Manual Volume 1;
An updated and descriptive Property Card be maintained by the Property Office;
Likewise, the Accounting Office is advised to maintain Property Equipment Ledger Cards as required under the NGAS to provide informative data on Property, Plant and Equipment;
For the year 2018, the Property Officer/Municipal Treasurer is advised to start issuing Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment (ARE) for the particular property issued to employees to easily pinpoint accountability and facilitate inventory taking; and
The cost of the school building shall be transferred to the Department of Education through a Journal Entry Voucher to be drawn by the Municipal Accountant and given to the Accountant of the DepEd.

13.9 We have recommended the following:
Ensure that expenditures are limited only to what is appropriated;
Ensure that the required registries are maintained by the Municipal Accountant or the Budget Officer to prevent the incurrence of expenditures in excess of allotments;
Prepare the Municipal Budget in such a way that actual needs of the municipality are properly included and allocated with funds in the budget; and
The Obligation Requests which is the basis for recording of obligations in the registries should be properly accomplished and the four RAAOs should be maintained and updated to facilitate monitoring of expenses and balances of appropriations.

We have recommended the following:
The Municipal Mayor create a committee to conduct physical count of inventories and PPE to determine actual existence and condition of the assets pursuant to Section 124 of the NGAS Manual Volume 1;
The property office/officer maintain property cards and ensure that the same is regularly updated;
The Accounting Office maintain Supplies and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards as required under the NGAS; and
After the conduct of physical count of PPE, the Accounting Office should compute for the depreciation using the estimated useful life under COA Circular No. 2003-007.

We have recommended the following:
The agency head require the Municipal Accountant-Designate to furnish the Audit Team a copy of the RA 7171 AIP;
That management submit written justification for the payments of infrastructures without the indispensable attachments;
That management submit the lacking documents for evaluation and review; and
Henceforth, the Municipal Accountant see to it that all disbursement vouchers are properly supported with complete documentation before any payment is made.
